<h2>3. Schedule your year.</h2>

<p>The most successful pilot teachers had a plan for each unit and when each unit would fall in the year. If you are teaching CS Principles as an AP course, it is important to know where you have extra time and where you need to pick up the pace. Planning your year gives you the freedom to adjust as necessary. Use our <a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1FSg2KuSecDN08Q88GIedZrGvZd3bVX1Ik19lLYEu9r4/preview", target=_"blank">Planning and Pacing Guide</a>, along with your school calendar, to start planning.</p>

